result.name: Sushi Senju

reviews.text: Happened to come for lunch on a Saturday and was not aware that it was under the same group of Ana Gura in Festival Walk which I did not really like.  Offered really similar dishes if not identical.  Food was OK, sea urchin excluded.  Floor staff were rather attentive in the beginning.  Not so much when more diners arrived.  They offered baskets here for you to put your bags under the seat, which Ana Gura failed altogether.  It happened an order for a plate of assorted sushi was misplaced.  That took unforgivably long for them to redo it.  I couldn’t understand why that long time needed when they were in real need to redo it quick to express their apology, which they never showed anyway.  Definitely not a place I can comfortably recommend if you want seriously good sushi.  Certainly my last and only visit.  If not for the attentive service in the very beginning, this place warranted no more than 1 star.

This is a corporate Lubuds own Japanese restaurant. No doubt on the food taste. Very nice restaurant but a bit tight. You can ask the chiefs any recommendations of the day when you are on the bar table. Yeah price is in mid range. Good to try.
Food was well prepared and fresh. Location and restaurant design is more like a mall cafe so doesn't warrant the high end prices
Lunch set is worth to eat. And sashimi is really fresh.
Not fine dining sushi (fish sliced in big chunk) but tasty and clean. Friendly staff.

reviews.text: Yes, it is another building for shopping and dinning. Once you jump on here, you can spend all your day long here shopping luxury goods, watching movies, and enjoying and dinning from luxury high end cuisine to budget restaurant and even sweety desert. And there are supermarket and small souvenirs shops too. There are some shops where you may experience only this place.
most convenient shopping mall with great restaurants

Very nice song mall with a wide array of styles of shops and levels of cost. It also has a cinema inside, several floors for restaurants and tea/dessert options, as well as four luxury restaurants with harbour views at the very top floors. Always a pleasant place and an option when around TST.
One stop for shopping and restaurants for every taste and any budget

Facing both nathan road and granville road corner. Nearest MTR station is Tsim Sha Tsui station Exit B2.
